Tracheal camerae distally contracted (
Fig. 50L
). Central lobe weak and incised (
Fig. 50M
). Laterostigmata II– IV large, II–III with no inner structures, but IV with a weak spot (
Fig. 50N
); those on V and VI small. On female squama genitalis (
Figs. 50A, B
) caput processus of duck’s head-type or curved towards median edge, filum processus long, proximo-lateral and median sclerotizations distinct. Male squama genitalis with long basiperiphallar setae (
Fig. 51C
).

Diagnosis. This new species is similar to
E. kantoense
in many respects, but the present species (body and foretarsus length 553–773 and 70–73 µm, respectively) is distinctly smaller than
E. kantoense
(1098–1339 and 108–123 µm, respectively). Further it differs from the latter in the absence of cephalic seta aa (present in
E. kantoense
), the shape of simple seta rs (inflated in
E. kantoense
), small spatulate foretarsal sensilla t2 and b'2 (long and narrowly spatulate in
E. kantoense
), the position of a' at the same level with α 3 (distal to α
3 in
E. kantoense
) and four pairs of anterior setae on abdominal tergite IV (five pairs in
E. kantoense
).
